# Showcase regeneration on every new card kind

`src/adapters/showcaseSeed.ts` is the **single fresh-kiosk seed**: it must
demo every visible card kind on one focused view. Whenever a strand adds a
new node kind (e.g. `WorkflowNode`, `PictureNode`, `URLNode`, future
`...Node`), the showcase MUST be regenerated as part of the same strand,
otherwise the new kind has no first-class demo surface and the operator
cannot see it on a fresh boot.

## Mandatory regeneration scope

Whenever a new kind lands, redo the showcase end-to-end:

1. **Theme**: a 6-panel **Obeya for a Data Platform Team**. Six top-level
   panels under the root; the panel set stays stable across regenerations
   so e2e fixtures keep resolving against the same panel slugs:
   `reliability`, `ingestion`, `infra-cost`, `products`, `team-health`,
   `workflow`.
2. **Combine cards** — every existing node kind must appear at least
   once across the six panels. Distribute the new kind into the panel
   that best matches its semantics; resist adding a seventh panel.
3. **Vary children per panel** — child counts must span the realistic
   operator range (3, 4, and 5 children represented across panels). Do
   not make every panel the same size.
4. **Vary values** — for the historisable kinds (`BusinessScoreNode`,
   `ComputedBusinessScoreNode`, `TextNode`, `WorkflowNode`), the value
   distribution must include:
   - at least one node with a multi-point history,
   - at least one node above objective and one below,
   - at least one node with a single point (no history),
   - at least one node with `setDisabled(true)`,
   - every `WorkflowStatus` (`plan`, `do`, `check`, `act`) used at least
     once on a `WorkflowNode`.
5. **Update unit + e2e tests in the same commit**:
   - `src/test/unit/adapters/showcaseSeed.test.ts` — assert the new
     panel set, the kind-coverage matrix, the disabled flag, the
     historised samples, and the four PDCA statuses.
   - `src/test/e2e/features/boot/app_boots.feature` — keep the root
     title scenario in sync with the new root title.
   - Any other e2e features that resolve against showcase IDs (grep for
     the panel slugs above before merging).
6. **Stable IDs**: the root stays `showcase-root` and the six panel ids
   stay stable (`reliability`, `ingestion`, `infra-cost`, `products`,
   `team-health`, `workflow`). Children under each panel may evolve to
   accommodate the new kind, but the panel-level slugs MUST NOT churn.

## Trigger checklist

Trigger this rule whenever ANY of the following is true:

- A new file lands under `src/domain/nodes/*Node.ts`.
- A new `kind` literal is added to the view-model union, the wire
  encoder, or `inferV4Kind`.
- A new `BusinessScoreCard`-derived subclass is introduced.

If you are touching such a file, regenerate the showcase in the same
strand. Do not defer it as a follow-up.
